The following months, however, showed that the Bush strategy, based on military recommendations, was the only possible and very successful one, so far, that the news about Iraq no longer speaks at all.
This did not improve Bush's reputation, for objectively he left his successor with a much more appreciative starting point than was expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes that the miracle will be repeated.
The military once again asked him to increase the contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of Afghanistan's operation General Stanley McCristal, who, despite his subordination habits, strongly criticized the timid shooters in the White House.
