The president hesitated for three months, but didn't come up with a better idea, so he cheated on the general wenist for 10,000 soldiers.
From Europe, he has pressed the pledge for another 5,000, even though he himself originally expected at least 10,000.
His intention to withdraw troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and to complete this process within three years is highly problematic in the whole Obama strategy. The whole Obama doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the halved increase will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Even in spite of the fratricidal war of recent years, the Iraq society is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is characterized by contraindication - nobody can be relied on and no agreements are kept.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces who are used to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they were formally established correctly, remain only bogus structures, behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the ambiguity of the conditions that further complicate Pakistan and Iran's influence.
The building of a "capable state", which is the minimalist goal of the entire operation, is also very unrealistic.
Time horizon of Obama’s strategy puzzled by its voluntarism
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only deteriorated further and now it is on the verge of the explosion.
Believe in the fact that the little soldiers, who broke out in the war cry about the "early homecoming", create a miracle here, can only a really romantic soul, which cannot be impressed by facts.
From a political point of view, the date for the withdrawal of troops is pure irresponsibility, because the Taliban will accept this as the indirect confession of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that the willingness of Europeans to participate in the fighting in Afghanistan is running out.
Europe's politicians cannot and do not want to explain to their voters how the security of Germany or Italy is linked to the war in the Hindu Kush foothills.
