CNMV approves Paternina's public exclusion notice submitted by the investment company Mer
The National Stock Exchange Commission (CNMV) approved the public tender submitted by the investment company Mer for Federico Paternina last October 9th.
The supervisory authority stated that it had approved this tender after it had been demonstrated that the conditions complied with the laws in force and that the content of the explanatory supplement submitted, following the amendments of 2 December last, could be considered "sufficient".
CNMV also announced that this offer is aimed at the acquisition of 550,0008 shares of Federico Paternina at a price of EUR 7.65 per share, which is 8.95 % of the capital of the company, which consists of EUR 6,142,786 in shares admitted to the Madrid and Bilbao stock exchanges.
It was also announced that 5,592,778 million shares have been fixed, which cannot be transferred in any way until the closing of the tender and whose price has been fixed by Federico Paternina in accordance with the laws in force.
New vehicle assessment programmes
In these days of storms and accidents not only the car workshops earn
Every day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are towed to the workshops, where an expert assesses the damage caused and the cost of the repair.
Not a single accident is the same and calculating the cost of parts and working hours can be a lengthy and complicated task.
The calculation of repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including parts and working hours, can take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest computer tools, it is a matter of minutes
That is why almost 100% of the experts use this type of system.
Service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs collect the information they receive from manufacturers in order to process them afterwards and to offer them to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American Solera group, is the market leader; 80% of all reviews are made with their products.
The other two companies that compete with the tool market for peer review and reporting are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is far from easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers are working together, each of them providing the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is increasing, to the point that in the last five years even more versions, variants and motorisations have been introduced to the market than in the entire fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car comes onto the market, the work begins for the companies.
It is a laborious task, because every one of the thousands of vehicle parts must be catagolized and its price entered.
In addition, each model creates an "intelligent" graphic image on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much-sold model, the work can be completed in a week if the process proceeds quickly.
If this is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the vehicle park on the roads, it is over 99%.
In order to carry out documentation work and to produce databases, Audatex has eight distributed centres worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in certain brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics specialists) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros a year in the development of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers receive the updates every other day.
The development of this enormous flow of information enables companies to use it in different ways and thus to offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but depending on the country, there are also tools for managing scrap parts or for calculating the price of a car.
The only company that informs about a leader about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex offers this offer not in Spain, but in the United States.
When looking through the products Audatex offers, it is easy to get an overview of the kind of support it provides to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, the star of which is AudaPlus, a standard solution for assessing accidents for the reviewers.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles as well as light and heavy industrial vehicles.
Apart from the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the painting prices.
This tool is paid according to the purpose of use, i.e. for each report.
It is the most expensive for customers who rarely use it, a maximum of ten times a month, namely 5.75 euros per month.
On the other hand, every insurance company that produces thousands of reports negotiates the price with Audatex.
With other products, such as AudaVIN, you can fully identify a vehicle and the equipment with which it ran from the assembly line, using the chassis number alone.
AudaGlass deals with the vehicle windows, and AudaSubastas is an open service on the Internet for the specialist market, with which one can offer for vehicles that have been declared total damage.
